    "title" : "javadoc -locale is invalid on version 17 and 25？",
    "body" : "<p>Locale setting is invalid on javadoc 17 and 25:</p>\n<pre><code>javadoc -locale en_US -sourcepath .\\src\\main\\java -subpackages my.packages -Xdoclint:none\n</code></pre>\n<p>It always output with my native lanuage rather than english. In javadoc 8, it's OK.</p>\n<p>How to set english for javadoc 17 and 25?</p>\n<p><strong>This Problem is Solved!</strong></p>\n<p><strong>HTML language</strong> and <strong>title language</strong> are controlled by different arguments, <strong>html lang</strong> is controlled by <code>-locale</code>, title content is controlled by <strong>JVM args</strong>, using -J can override jvm args:</p>\n<pre><code>javadoc &quot;-J-Duser.language=en&quot; &quot;-J-Duser.country=US&quot; -locale en-US\n</code></pre>\n<p>In gradle, using:</p>\n<pre><code>  val ops = options as StandardJavadocDocletOptions\n  ops.encoding = &quot;UTF-8&quot;\n  ops.locale = &quot;en-us&quot;\n  ops.charSet = &quot;UTF-8&quot;\n  ops.docEncoding = &quot;UTF-8&quot;\n  ops.jFlags(&quot;-Duser.language=en&quot;, &quot;-Duser.country=US&quot;)\n  ops.addBooleanOption(&quot;Xdoclint:none&quot;, true)\n</code></pre>\n<p><a href=\"https://i.sstatic.net/9nbjXlvK.png\" rel=\"nofollow noreferrer\"><img src=\"https://i.sstatic.net/9nbjXlvK.png\" alt=\"enter image description here\" /></a></p>\n",
