    "question_id" : 79804364,
    "body" : "<p>Starting with JDK 17, the <code>javadoc</code> tool became stricter about how it handles the <code>-locale</code> option.<br />\nOlder versions (like Java 8 or 11) accepted locale codes such as <code>es_MX</code>, but newer versions validate locales using the IETF BCP 47 standard — the same format used by</p>\n<p>Solution:<br />\nUse a hyphen (<code>-</code>) instead of an underscore when specifying the locale:</p>\n<pre><code>javadoc -locale es-MX\n</code></pre>\n",
